HEADWORD: Uxoricide
<hw>Ux*or"i*cide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>uxor</ets> wife + <ets>caedere</ets> to kill.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The murder of a wife by her husband.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who murders his wife.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uxorious</ent>⟦br⟧
